<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Furlcalling Finger Remedy Crafting Guide in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>To craft the <strong>Furlcalling Finger Remedy</strong> you need the following <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Materials" href="/Materials" target="">Crafting Materials</a>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Erdleaf Flower" href="/Erdleaf+Flower" target="">Erdleaf Flower</a> x2</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3>Other Ways of obtaining Furlcalling Finger Remedy</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Helping a host kill a boss earns you a Furlcalling Finger Remedy</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Furlcalling Finger Remedy Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>You can hold up to 999 <strong>Furlcalling Finger Remedy</strong>.</li> 
 <li>With a Furlcalling Finger Remedy, you can see summon signs, which can be used to summon players from other worlds. (Finger Remedies are consumed with use.)</li> 
 <li>While Furlcalling Finger Remedy is active, player will be unable to use Spirit Summons via the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spirit Calling Bell" href="/Spirit+Calling+Bell">Spirit Calling Bell </a></li> 
 <li>There are various types of summon signs. Gold signs summon Furled Finger cooperators. Red signs summon duelist adversaries. (For either type of multiplayer, the summoning player becomes Host of Fingers.)</li> 
 <li>Assuming you haven't already summoned another player, using the Furlcalling Finger Remedy a second time will give you the option to cancel the remedy, refunding the spent Furlcalling Finger Remedy.</li> 
 <li>If you die before successfully summoning, the Furlcalling Finger Remedy will be refunded.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Sell Value: <img style="width: 18px; height: 18px;" title="er-runes-13" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18"> 10 <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes">Runes</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3>Elden Ring Furlcalling Finger Remedy Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>You can hold up to 999 <strong>Furlcalling Finger Remedies.</strong></li> 
 <li>You can't store <strong>Furlcalling Finger Remedies.</strong></li> 
 <li>You cannot drop <strong>Furlcalling Finger Remedy</strong> for other players during multiplayer. If you or a co-op partner needs a Furlcalling Finger Remedy, instead drop them <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Erdleaf Flower" href="/Erdleaf+Flower">Erdleaf Flowers</a>, then craft a remedy.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
